[[Ganymede (moon)|Ganymede]] is the largest [[natural satellite|moon]] in the [[solar system]], and thus has many [[Impact crater|craters]] covering its hard surface.  Here is a list of Ganymedean craters that have been given names.  Most are named after figures from Egyptian, Mesopotamian, and other ancient Middle Eastern myths.

