{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}
{{BLP sources|date=January 2008}}
'''Sujoy Kumar Guha''' is an Indian [[biomedical engineering|biomedical engineer]]. He was born in [[Patna]], [[India]], 20 June 1940.<ref name=iitkgp>[http://www.iitkgp.ac.in/top-awardees/daa1.php?Sl=73 Distinguished Alumnus of IIT Kharagpur] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411033855/http://www.iitkgp.ac.in/top-awardees/daa1.php?Sl=73 |date=11 April 2016 }}, retrieved 2015-04-23.</ref>

He did his undergraduate degree (''B.Tech.'') in [[electrical engineering]] from [[IIT Kharagpur]], followed by a master's degree in electrical engineering at IIT, and another [[Master's degree]] from the [[University of Illinois]], Urbana-Champaign. He later received his [[Ph.D.]] in medical [[physiology]] from [[St. Louis University]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Gifford|first=Bill|title=The Revolutionary New Birth Control Method for Men|url=https://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/04/ff_vasectomy/all/1|work=Wired May 2011|publisher=Wired Magazine|accessdate=2012-05-31}}</ref>  He then founded the Centre for Biomedical Engineering [https://web.archive.org/web/20060518045542/http://www.iitd.ac.in/center/cbme/], [[IIT Delhi]] and [[All India Institute of Medical Sciences|AIIMS]] and also obtained his [[Bachelors of Medicine and Surgery|MBBS]] degree from [[Delhi University]]. One of the founders of biomedical engineering in India, Prof. Guha is internationally known in the areas of [[Physical therapy|rehabilitation]] engineering, [[bioengineering]] in reproductive medicine and technology for rural health care. He has received several [[award]]s and has more than 100 [[research]] papers in cited journals. In 2003 he became a chair professor at IIT Kharagpur.<ref name=iitkgp/>

His major contributions have been in the invention and development of non-hormonal polymer based injectable [[male contraceptive]] ([[RISUG]]) for which the Final Phase-III Clinical trials are underway;{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} Problem-solving at a national level regarding [[contraceptives]] in mass usage, especially [[Intrauterine device|Copper T]]; {{citation needed|date=April 2015}}individualized spot air-conditioning system for hospital patients and rehabilitation of the blind, with emphasis on opening automobile repair as an employment avenue.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}

